text: standardlastprofile package contains one dataset called load_profiles used plot . contains 9.504 observations 5 variables. Given ‘weekday’ ‘period’ data load_profiles given ‘profile’ represents ‘typical day’, e.g. Sunday winter versus working day summer. 11 load profiles 3 customer groups: idea “H0” etc. stands , alone. H0: households (German: “Haushalte”) G0 G6: commerce (“Gewerbe”) L0 L2: agriculture (“Landwirtschaft”) Call get_load_profile_info() information examples. can use function get_load_profile() generate time series given profile. algorithm sets December 24 31 ‘saturday’, public holiday ‘sunday’ – Sunday. title: Generate a load profile — get_load_profile
text: load profile describes consumption profile electricity consumer certain period time. Given start date, end date profile, function maps date 'typical day', returns load profile requested period. typical day combination 'working_day', 'saturday', 'sunday', period, .e. 'summer', 'winter', 'transition'. Supported profiles : H0: households (German: "Haushalte") G0 G6: commerce ("Gewerbe") L0 L2: agriculture ("Landwirtschaft") Call get_load_profile_info() information profiles. addition, distinction made three different type days: 'working_day': Monday Friday 'saturday': Saturdays; Dec 24th Dec 31th considered 'saturday' , 'sunday' 'sunday': Sundays public holidays Periods defined BDEW: summer: May 15 September 14 winter: November 1 March 20 transition: March 21 May 14, September 15 October 31

what: standardlastprofile: Data on Load Profiles for Electricity from BDEW — standardlastprofile-package
title: standardlastprofile: Data on Load Profiles for Electricity from BDEW — standardlastprofile-package
text: load profile describes consumption profile electricity consumer certain period time. electricity customers without modern meter devices, energy utility uses standardised load profiles (SLP). SLPs replace non-existent load profile end consumers calculated, sufficiently accurate forecast electricity consumption 15-minutes basis. packages provides data German Association Energy Water Industries (BDEW Bundesverband der Energie- und Wasserwirtschaft e.V.) tidy format. eleven profiles, 96 quarter-hourly values included three different days week - working day, Saturday, Sunday - three different seasons - summer, winter, transition -, .e. total 3x3x96 observations per profile.
